Title: Episode 126 - Slimming Down .NET: The Unofficial Experiments of Michal Strehovský
Description: Listeners are taken on a journey with Michal Strehovsky, a developer on the .NET runtime team who has been experimenting with reducing the size of .NET applications. Strehovsky shares his personal projects BFlat and Flattened.NET that allow .NET developers to play with the technology and non-.NET developers to get into .NET. Through the use of unsupported territories and ahead-of-time compilation, Strehovsky was able to create a self-contained WinForms Snake game in C# that was under 8KB in size. This podcast is a must-listen for anyone interested in reducing the size of their .NET applications and exploring the versatility of the technology
